19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 69 O.S. 2021, Section 1521, as
21 amended by Section 1, Chapter 460, O.S.L. 2025 (69 O.S. Supp. 2025,
22 Section 1521), is amended to read as follows:
23 Section 1521. A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury
24 a fund to be known as the “Rebuilding Oklahoma Access and Driver
SB1309 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Safe ty Fund” (ROADS Fund). The fund shall be a continuing fund, not
2 subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all
3 appropriations and transfers made by the Legislature. All monies
4 accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby appropriated and may
5 be budgeted and expended by the Department of Transportation for the
6 purposes authorized by subsection D of this section in amounts as
7 authorized by the Oklahoma Legislature. Expenditures from the fund
8 shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against
9 claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
10 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
11 B. Beginning July 1, 2021, except for an amount equivalent to
12 the amount of revenue apportioned to the Rebuilding Oklahoma Access
13 and Driver Safety Fund pursuant to Section 500.4B of Title 68 and
14 Section 1104 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes and from other
15 sources apportioned to the ROADS Fund by law, there shall be
16 apportioned to the funds specified in this subsection from the
17 monies that would otherwise be apportioned to the General Revenue
18 Fund by Section 2352 of Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes from the
19 revenues derived pursuant to subsections A, B, and E of Section 2355
20 of Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes amounts as follows:
21 1. Subject to any reductions required by subsection C of this
22 section, there shall be apportioned to the Rebuilding Oklahoma
23 Access and Driver Safety Fund:
24
